### Platform-Specific Collection Methods

**LinkedIn** (profile: `ot-linkedin`):
- Navigate to linkedin.com/in/{{handle.linkedin}}/recent-activity/all/
- For each post: extract reactions, comments, reposts from post containers
- For articles: navigate to individual article, check stats
- LinkedIn analytics dashboard: linkedin.com/dashboard — impressions, profile views, search appearances

**Twitter/X** (profile: `ot-twitter`):
- Navigate to own profile → Posts tab
- For each tweet: extract views, likes, retweets, replies, bookmarks
- Twitter analytics: x.com/analytics (if available)

**Medium** (profile: `ot-medium`):
- Navigate to medium.com/me/stats
- Extract: views, reads, read ratio, fans (claps), responses per article

**Substack** (profile: `ot-substack`):
- Navigate to publication dashboard
- Extract: opens, open rate, clicks, subscribers gained per post

**Threads** (profile: `ot-threads`):
- Navigate to own profile
- For each post: extract likes, replies, reposts

**Reddit** (profile: `ot-reddit`):
- Navigate to user profile / recent posts
- Extract: upvotes, comments, upvote ratio per post/comment

**Dev.to** (profile: `ot-devto`):
- Navigate to dev.to/dashboard
- Extract: views, reactions, comments per article

**Indie Hackers** (profile: `ot-ih`):
- Navigate to own profile
- Extract: upvotes, comments per post

**Product Hunt** (profile: `ot-ph`):
- Navigate to own profile
- Extract: upvotes, comments on any launches/discussions

